President Obama announced his intent to nominate Dr. Lanhee J. Chen to a key Administration post as a Member of the Social Security Advisory Board. Dr. Chen is a Research Fellow at the Hoover Institution, Lecturer in Public Policy at Stanford University, and Lecturer in Law at Stanford Law School. He has previously served as the Policy Director for the Romney-Ryan presidential campaign, Governor Romney's chief policy adviser, and a senior strategist on the campaign. Dr. Chen has also held positions such as Deputy Campaign Manager and Policy Director for Steve Poizner's California gubernatorial campaign, Associate Attorney at Gibson, Dunn & Crutcher LLP, and Senior Counselor to the Deputy Secretary at the U.S. Department of Health and Human Services. He has a background in health policy and has worked as a health policy advocate for the ERISA Industry Committee. Dr. Chen holds degrees from Harvard College, Harvard University, and Harvard Law School.